# ============================================================================
# NOTES
# ============================================================================
#
# Music Library Structure:
# Your music should be organized in subdirectories by tag/genre:
#   /path/to/music/
#   ├── pop/
#   │   ├── Artist - Song1.mp3
#   │   └── Artist - Song2.mp3
#   ├── rock/
#   ├── jazz/
#   ├── ambient/
#   └── etc/
#
# Interstitials Directory Structure:
#   /path/to/interstitials/
#   ├── morning/
#   │   ├── morning-promo-1.mp3
#   │   └── morning-promo-2.mp3
#   ├── evening/
#   │   ├── evening-intro.mp3
#   │   └── evening-announcement.mp3
#   └── party/
#       ├── party-hype.mp3
#       └── weekend-special.mp3
#
# Interstitials Probability Examples:
#   - 0.0 = Never play interstitials
#   - 0.2 = 20% chance (roughly 1 in 5 songs)
#   - 0.5 = 50% chance (every other song on average)
#   - 1.0 = Always play after every song
#
# After creating your station config, scan it with:
#   python -m radio.scan_media --db /path/to/radio.db \
#     --music /path/to/music --stations stations/MYCALL.toml

